<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="14" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d14fn1">Channel of transmission not indicated.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-28">28 June 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to
                            President. Personal and secret. No. 334.</p>
                        <p>I send you first of all the very unpleasant reply I have received from
                                <gloss target="#t_UJ1">U. J.</gloss> and my rejoinder.<note n="2" xml:id="d14fn2">Neither printed herein. The exchange concerned the
                                second front.</note> This certainly has its bearing on your proposal
                            to meet him alone and I shall not seek to deter you if you can get him
                            to come.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>